neoash
======

Standalone Autotools-based extraction of the FreeBSD sh shell from chimerautils.


Policy:
======

This fork is POSIX-first.

The yash POSIX suite under test-posix/yash is the primary correctness
gate for the project. The imported FreeBSD sh regression suite under
test-posix/freebsd is a secondary guardrail used to catch accidental
breakage while POSIX fixes land.

When POSIX behavior conflicts with historical FreeBSD behavior, POSIX
wins by default. Yash behavior and the POSIX text are the main
day-to-day reference points for compliance work. Dash may be useful as
an extra comparison point, but it is not the primary model.


Build:
=====

$ autoreconf -fi
$ ./configure
$ make

Build without libedit history and line editing:

$ ./configure --without-libedit
$ make


Run:
===

$ ./src/sh -c 'echo ok'


Test:
====

Primary POSIX scoreboard:

$ make TESTEE=./src/sh test-posix-report

Faster non-signal POSIX pass:

$ make TESTEE=./src/sh test-posix-nosignal-report

Secondary FreeBSD guardrail:

$ make TESTEE=./src/sh test-posix-freebsd

Convenience aliases:

$ make TESTEE=./src/sh test-primary
$ make TESTEE=./src/sh test-guardrail


Layout:
======

- src/         shell core plus generator inputs and scripts
- src/bltin/   builtin implementations (echo, kill, printf, test)
- src/compat/  minimal portability shims used by this extracted tree
- include/     compatibility headers copied from chimerautils


Provenance:
==========

See UPSTREAM.md for the exact upstream commit and copied paths.
